So you have two practical options:
Option A: Use ECDSA P-256 through SignServer — fully supported with the soft crypto token, and the W3C Data Integrity spec defines ecdsa-jcs-2019 as a standard cryptosuite. This keeps SignServer as your key custodian.
Option B: Handle Ed25519 entirely in Django (using PyNaCl or the cryptography library) — gives you eddsa-jcs-2022 proofs but SignServer is bypassed for signing.
Both produce valid, verifiable DID document proofs per W3C specs.Q: Which approach do you want to go with?
